Definitely agree =E2=80=93 I=E2=80=99ve read a few articles in the past =
few days suggesting that organisations will be more fluid with groups =
coming together in project teams rather than hierarchical teams =
=E2=80=93 these project teams can meet in the office as appropriate but =
are better suited to remote working.

This hopefully will break down the parental attitude to culture and the =
practice of only involving line managers in disseminating culture =
=E2=80=93 promoting the need to have adult to adult cultural =
conversations =E2=80=93 and to consolidate performance feedback across a =
wider variety of colleagues who have had interactions. (We=E2=80=99ll =
also need to ask for an input to tell us which teams individuals are =
working within so we know how to ask for feedback =E2=80=93 but =
presumably companies will use some sort of software to co-ordinate teams =
(to a certain extent replacing line managers).

The future is ours=E2=80=A6=E2=80=A6=E2=80=A6=E2=80=A6. or alternatively =
companies will go back to their old ways, but think (hope) enforced =
social distancing over [ 9 to 12 ] months will stop that.

C

